  "original_title": "UNICEF Regional Director for South Asia meets Foreign Minister",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "UNICEF Regional Director for South Asia meets Foreign Minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The UNICEF Regional Director for South Asia, George Laryea-Adjei, who is currently on a visit to Sri Lanka, paid a courtesy call on the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Ali Sabry on Wednesday.",
        "Foreign Minister Sabry appreciated the cooperation and assistance extended by UNICEF to Sri Lanka.",
        "Particular attention was paid to projects related to early childhood development, health and nutrition, immunization, safe water and sanitization, education and skills building, social welfare policies, and COVID-19 response.",
        "The Regional Director apprised Foreign Minister Sabry of \u00a0UNICEF programs in the country, particularly efforts undertaken to assist Sri Lanka during the current challenges.",
        "The Minister welcomed the new UNICEF country program to be implemented in 2023.",
        "He further stated that Sri Lanka has been a benchmark in its efforts in providing free healthcare, education as well as other social security measures due to which the Human Development Index for Sri Lanka is well above the regional average.",
        "The Regional Director appreciated the efforts taken by the Government of Sri Lanka for the protection and well-being of children in Sri Lanka and assured the continued cooperation and assistance of UNICEF to Sri Lanka.",
        "\u201cI\u2019d love to speak like I used to, but I cannot,\u201d \u2013 Ranjan talks to the press after released from prison",
        "SJB wants full Presidential Pardon for Ranjan Ramanayake with Political Rights"
      ],
